[
  "10:24 a.m. | The Artemis II launch team initiated liquid hydrogen (LH2) topping for the SLS core stage.",
  "10:35 a.m. | The Artemis II launch team began liquid hydrogen (LH2) replenish for the SLS core stage.",
  "11:09 a.m. | NASA teams have begun the topping phase for the interim cryogenic propulsion stage liquid hydrogen (LH2) tank.",
  "11:15 a.m. | NASA teams have transitioned the interim cryogenic propulsion stage liquid hydrogen tank to replenish mode.",
  "11:42 a.m. | NASA teams are in fast fill of liquid oxygen (LOX) into the interim cryogenic propulsion stage as part of the Artemis II launch countdown.",
  "12:03 p.m. | NASA teams are now maintaining the liquid oxygen levels in the SLS rocket core stage through replenish mode.",
  "12:23 p.m. | Liquid oxygen (LOX) fast fill is now complete for the SLS upper stage.",
  "12:40 p.m. | NASA\u2019s Artemis II astronauts received a final weather briefing inside the Astronaut Crew Quarters.",
  "12:51 p.m. | With NASA teams now maintaining the liquid oxygen levels in the interim cryogenic propulsion, all cryogenic stages of the SLS rocket have transitioned to replenish mode.",
  "1:15 p.m. | NASA astronauts Reid Wiseman, Victor Glover, and Christina Koch, along with CSA astronaut Jeremy Hansen, are suiting up inside the Astronaut Crew Quarters.",
  "1:36 p.m. | NASA\u2019s pad rescue and closeout crew teams have arrived at Launch Complex 39B.",
  "2:00 p.m. | Just moments ago, NASA\u2019s Artemis II flight crew began the walk that every NASA astronaut has made since Apollo 7, heading to the elevator and down through the double doors.",
  "2:14 p.m. | NASA\u2019s Artemis II crew arrived at Launch Complex 39B where the SLS rocket with Orion spacecraft stands ready for launch.",
  "2:27 p.m. | With assistance from the closeout crew, the Artemis II crew are carefully donning their helmets and gloves.",
  "2:31 p.m. | NASA\u2019s Artemis II crew members are boarding the agency\u2019s Orion spacecraft to begin communication checks.",
  "3:17 p.m. | NASA\u2019s Artemis II closeout crew is now completing preparing and closing the crew module hatch to the Orion spacecraft.",
  "3:39 p.m. | NASA engineers have conducted counterbalance mechanism operations and are now performing hatch seal pressure decay checks inside the White Room.",
  "4:02 p.m. | Technicians began installing the crew module hatch service panel on the Orion spacecraft."
